{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a6fd7c4a-c550-49db-9d41-356b1eeb1bdd","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n## 1. Deep Import Chain\nThe project imports `level1.props` → which imports `level2.props` → which imports `level3.props`. Each nested import adds evaluation overhead because MSBuild must resolve, parse, and evaluate each file sequentially during the **evaluation phase**. Deep chains slow down project load, especially in large solutions.\n\n## 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob scans the entire directory tree. It only excludes `bin/` and `obj/`, meaning it will crawl into `.git/`, `node_modules/`, or any other large directories. This causes expensive filesystem enumeration during evaluation. **Fix**: restrict to specific extensions/directories or add patterns to `DefaultItemExcludes`.\n\n## 3. File I/O via Property Function During Evaluation\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nThis reads a file from disk during the **evaluation phase** using a property function. Evaluation should be fast and purely declarative; file I/O belongs in the **execution phase** (e.g., inside a `<Target>`). Every time the project is evaluated (IDE load, design-time builds, restore), this I/O is triggered.\n\n## Evaluation vs. Execution Phase\nMSBuild's **evaluation phase** processes properties, items, and imports to build the project model — it runs on every load/reload. The **execution phase** runs targets and tasks. Expensive operations (I/O, globs over huge trees, deep import chains) during evaluation multiply their cost because evaluation happens far more frequently than builds.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e13121f6-3b17-4e9e-8606-a3b9350b7c1b","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"DBC7:14859A:ABFE1D2:BAE4840:69FD39CF"},"id":"3fcadf18-9ee0-4fd1-b9a3-40ff00e3e948","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:18:18.782Z","parentId":"6609833f-91a4-4be6-b0d2-a80f1b18c654"}
